post_text: MDOT announced that the 100th Street Bridge project will begin Monday, March 23: 100th Street will be closed to through-traffic between S. Kent Drive and Division Avenue with traffic detoured on Clyde Park Avenue, 84th Street, and Division Avenue. Traffic will be maintained on US-131 with traffic shifts and lane closures. Short-term closures for bridge demolition, beam setting, and paving will be in effect on US-131. Traffic will exit and re-enter the highway using the 100th Street off and on ramps. Alternating ramp closures will be in effect and traffic detoured to the adjacent interchanges at 142nd Avenue to the south and 84th Street to the north. The project is slated to be complete in October 2020.
